A US FDA complete response letter has delayed the potential approval of Zircaix. However, we see the valuation impact as modest, with the risk/reward outlook attractive at current levels.
The US FDA has requested additional data to establish comparability between Zircaix as used in the ZIRCON trial and the process intended for commercial use.
Existing clinical data for product comparability has the potential to be used for resubmission without another substantial trial.
We delay the assumed approval of Zircaix to 2H26, but with no change to longerterm assumptions or valuation risk weighting.
We value Precision Medicine at \(A\) 14.30/share. At the current share price (A \(14.95/share), this implies limited value to the Therapeutics pipeline. Retain OW.

Zircaix approval delayed: TLX has received a Complete Response Letter (CRL) from the FDA in relation to Zircaix (focused on the diagnosis and characterisation of renal masses as clear cell renal carcinoma). Key issues raised in the CRL: 1) Comparability between the product used in the Phase III ZIRCON trial and the product manufactured for commercial use. TLX sees existing analytical and clinical comparability data as potentially sufficient to support resubmission without a further substantial trial. 2) Two third-party suppliers of raw API and intermediate drug processing have received notices of quality deficiency that are required to be remediated prior to resubmission of the application (BLA). 3) No safety or efficacy issues were raised as part of this CRL.

What we have changed: No specific timeline for resubmission or potential approval has been provided. We now assume approval in 2H26 (from 2H25), with outer- year assumptions unchanged combined with minor revisions to operating cost assumptions, this provides large revisions to near- term earnings (on a low base), but with average outer year changes \(Australia Healthcare | AustraliaStock RatingOverweightIndustry ViewIn-LinePrice targetA$25.60Up/downside to price target (%)71Shr price, close (Aug 28, 2025)A$14.9552-Week RangeA$31.97-13.94Sh out, dil, curr (mn)345Mkt cap, curr (mn)US$3,348EV, curr (mn)US$3,295Avg daily trading value (mn)A$37

Our price target is derived by applying probability weightings of \(70\%\) to our base- case valuation and \(15\%\) each to our bull and bear scenarios. Our base case captures approved products/TMS as well as risk- weighted contributions for late stage indications/candidates. We see balanced probabilities toward the upside captured within our bull case and downside captured in our bear case.

Our Overweight thesis reflects the attractive risk/reward outlook at current levels. We see scope for improved prostate cancer (PCa) imaging reimbursement for TLX as well as potential for new formulations and expanded indications. In the near term, we see potential for the approval of Zircaix (focused on the diagnosis of clear cell renal carcinoma/ccRCC), with interim data from the Phase III ProSAT Global trial expected later in 2025. We see the current share price as capturing contributions from Precision Medicine but with modest contributions from the Therapeutics pipeline.
